        By
        <span><a href="/person/n/joshua-q-nelson">Joshua Q. Nelson</a> <!----> <span class="article-source"><a href="https://www.foxnews.com" target="_blank"> | Fox News</a></span></span></span> <!----></div> <div class="article-social"><div class="social-icons"><ul><li class="fb"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Facebook</a></li> <li class="tw"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Twitter</a></li> <li class="flipboard"><a rel="nofollow">Flipboard</a></li> <li class="comments"><a href="#" rel="nofollow"><span>Comments</span></a></li> <li class="print"><a href="/politics/nikki-haley-calls-for-every-governor-in-america-to-ban-funding-for-critical-race-theory-in-schools.print" rel="nofollow">Print</a></li> <li class="email"><a href="#" rel="nofollow">Email</a></li></ul></div></div></div></header> <div class="article-content-wrap sticky-columns"><div class="article-content"><div class="article-body"><div class="featured featured-video video-ct" data-v-13907676><div class="contain" data-v-13907676><div class="control" data-v-13907676><a href="#" class="top" data-v-13907676></a> <a href="#" class="close" data-v-13907676>close</a></div> <div class="video-container" data-v-13907676><div data-video-id="6263420044001" data-video-domain="foxnews" data-widget-type="embed" class="m video-player" data-v-13907676><a href="http://video.foxnews.com/v/6263420044001" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute;" data-v-13907676><img src="https://a57.foxnews.com/cf-images.us-east-1.prod.boltdns.net/v1/static/694940094001/fce9ef3b-3245-48f7-b709-647a90e2f63d/0a139e38-3dfd-4bd8-bfe1-39dd2d2e6de0/1280x720/match/931/524/image.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1" alt="Nikki Haley: Every governor in America should ban funding for CRT in schools" data-v-13907676> <span class="overlay" data-v-13907676>Video</span></a></div></div> <div class="info" data-v-13907676><div class="caption" data-v-13907676><h4 class="title" data-v-13907676><a href="http://video.foxnews.com/v/6263420044001" data-v-13907676>Nikki Haley: Every governor in America should ban funding for CRT in schools</a></h4> <p data-v-13907676>Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley blasts critical race theory being taught in schools.</p></div></div></div></div><p class="speakable">Former U.N. Ambassador <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/category/person/nikki-haley" target="_blank">Nikki Haley</a> on Monday eviscerated <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/us/what-is-critical-race-theory" target="_blank">critical race theory</a>, calling for "every governor in the United States" to "ban" the racially charged academic movement.</p><div class="ad-container mobile ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="ban1" class="ad gam"></div></div><div class="ad-container tablet ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="lb2" class="ad gam"></div></div><p class="speakable">"Think about a 5-year-old that starts kindergarten and they don't know anything about color. If she's White, you're telling her she's bad. If she's Brown or Black, you’re telling her she will never be enough and she's always a victim. That's harmful for the well-being of our children," Haley told "<a href="https://www.foxnews.com/shows/america-reports" target="_blank">America Reports</a>."&nbsp;<br><br>Haley's comments come as <a href="https://www.foxnews.com/category/us/education" target="_blank">school districts nationwide</a> have been scrutinized by parents in recent months over CRT-themed topics being taught in some classrooms and CRT seminars being offered to teachers and administrations.&nbsp;</p><p>The former South Carolina governor argued that teaching critical race theory will have "long-lasting effects" on children. Moreover, Haley asserted critical race theory does not need to be taught to children in kindergarten as it is on the collegiate level.</p><div class="ad-container desktop ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="lb2" class="ad gam"></div></div><div class="embed-media twitter"><div class="tweet-embed"></div></div><p>Furthering her point, Haley recalled being "teased" as a kid for being Indian, sharing what her mother’s response was to the situation.</p><div class="ad-container mobile ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="ban2" class="ad gam"></div></div><p>"I remember getting teased when I was younger in rural South Carolina and my mom would say, 'Your job is to show them how you're similar and not how you’re different,'" Haley said.</p><div class="ad-container tablet ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="lb3" class="ad gam"></div></div><p><a href="https://www.foxnews.com/us/nikki-haley-critical-race-theory"><strong><u>NIKKI HALEY SLAMS CRITICAL RACE THEORY, SAYS AMERICA SHOULD NOT BE 'DIVIDED BY DIFFERENT SHADES OF COLOR'</u></strong></a></p><p>Haley doubled down on a tweet she posted last week arguing critical race theory will "hold generations of young people back." She called it harmful to young people and a general hurdle to uniting the country.&nbsp;</p><div class="ad-container mobile ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="ban3" class="ad gam"></div></div><p>"Critical race theory is going to hold back generations of young people," Haley wrote on Twitter.&nbsp;</p><p><a href="https://www.foxnews.com/apps-products"><strong><u>CLICK HERE FOR THE FOX NEWS APP</u></strong></a></p><div class="ad-container tablet ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="lb4" class="ad gam"></div></div><div type="video" caption="Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley discusses critical race theory, President Biden’s handling of Afghanistan, and Cuban protestors on ‘America Reports.’" originalImageUrl="https://cf-images.us-east-1.prod.boltdns.net/v1/static/694940094001/8339cdfb-c5b6-4c17-ba3a-0b69806b1068/bde176fb-961a-4615-95f0-35e03acd450f/1280x720/match/image.jpg" class="embed-media fn-video"><div class="video-container"><div data-video-id="6263420799001" data-video-domain="foxnews" data-widget-type="embed" class="m video-player" style="width: 100%; height: 100%;"><a href="http://video.foxnews.com/v/6263420799001" style="width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute;"><img src="https://a57.foxnews.com/cf-images.us-east-1.prod.boltdns.net/v1/static/694940094001/8339cdfb-c5b6-4c17-ba3a-0b69806b1068/bde176fb-961a-4615-95f0-35e03acd450f/1280x720/match/720/405/image.jpg?ve=1&amp;tl=1" alt="Nikki Haley on Cuban protestors calling for end of communism: ‘These people are desperate for freedom’"> <span class="overlay">Video</span></a></div></div></div><p>"Every governor in the country needs to ban funding for critical race theory. Governors can decide this. They decide what money they take from the Department of Education. Don’t take this money," Haley implored, adding that kids do not need to be judged when they go to school.&nbsp;</p><div class="ad-container mobile ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="ban4" class="ad gam"></div></div><div class="ad-container desktop ad-h-50 ad-w-300"><div data-iu="lb3" class="ad gam"></div></div><p>"They don't need to be told what label they are when they walk in the school. We need to treat kids as the opportunities they’re going to be to fix America, not break them before they start," Haley concluded.</p> <!----></div> <div class="article-meta"><div class="author-bio">Joshua Q. Nelson is a reporter for FoxNews.com. You can find him on Twitter @joshuaqnelson.</div></div> <footer class="article-footer"><!----> <!----> <div data-uid="ar-2" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div> <div data-uid="ar-3" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div> <div data-uid="ar-1" class="vendor-unit mobile"></div> <div class="vendor-unit vendor-yieldmo"><div class="ad-container mobile-tablet yieldmo"><div id="cu_article_4" class="ad cu"></div></div></div> <div class="vendor-unit vendor-yieldmo"><div id="cu_article_3" class="ad-container yieldmo"></div></div> <div data-uid="ar-8" class="vendor-unit tablet-desktop"></div> <!----> <!----> <div id="commenting" class="article-comments"></div></footer></div> <div class="sidebar sidebar-article sidebar-primary desktop"><div class="sticky-region"><div class="sidebar-columns"><div article-meta="[object Object